data.title: 197x Pontiac Astre
data.meta_description:
This is one I didn't even know existed.  Caught at the Richmond, Ontario, Sept 1st 2008 Auto Classic, I had no idea what it was until I looked it up.  "NOTAVEGA" is right: it's the (I think) Canadian built, Pontiac version of the Chevy Vega. (this is not unprecedented: the Pontiac Catalina was the Canadian built version of the Chev Caprice/Pontiac Parisienne)
	
	I don't know what exact year it is though.  It has, obviously, been heavily (and awesomely) modified.
